---
description: Architecture authority and dependency boundaries
alwaysApply: true
---

`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` is the single source of truth for the system architecture.

- If code and the architecture disagree, treat the code as wrong until an intentional architecture decision updates the document.
- Dependencies point inward: core must not import adapters, CLI code, or provider SDKs.
- Keep the canonical Document at the center of processing.
- Keep stages, ports, and adapters replaceable and limited to one responsibility.
- Never sacrifice the documented architecture for implementation speed.
